s.text: There are only 50 repertory theaters left in the United States and fewer old movies to see in them, since the tiny market leaves little incentive for the studios to strike new prints when old ones age and break.
College and museum film programmers report that they can't book any films on the AFI's top-100-movies-of-all-time list.
